about.summary: Build graph/network structures using functions for stepwise addition and deletion of nodes and edges. Work with data available in tables for bulk addition of nodes, edges, and associated metadata. Use graph selections and traversals to apply changes to specific nodes or edges. A wide selection of graph algorithms allow for the analysis of graphs. Visualize the graphs and take advantage of any aesthetic properties assigned to nodes and edges.

name: r-diagrammer
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.6.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-diagrammer
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/DiagrammeR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/DiagrammeR/DiagrammeR_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: be4e4c520a3692902ce405e8225aef9f3d5f0cd11fcde614f6541e981b63673d

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcolorbrewer >=1.1_2
    - r-downloader >=0.4
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.4
    - r-glue >=1.2.0
    - r-htmltools >=0.3.6
    - r-htmlwidgets >=1.0
    - r-igraph >=1.1.2
    - r-influencer >=0.1.0
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrr >=0.2.4
    - r-readr >=1.1.1
    - r-rgexf >=0.15.3
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-rstudioapi >=0.7
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-stringr >=1.3.0
    - r-tibble >=1.4.2
    - r-tidyr >=0.8.0
    - r-viridis >=0.5.0
    - r-visnetwork >=2.0.3
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rcolorbrewer >=1.1_2
    - r-downloader >=0.4
    - r-dplyr >=0.7.4
    - r-glue >=1.2.0
    - r-htmltools >=0.3.6
    - r-htmlwidgets >=1.0
    - r-igraph >=1.1.2
    - r-influencer >=0.1.0
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrr >=0.2.4
    - r-readr >=1.1.1
    - r-rgexf >=0.15.3
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-rstudioapi >=0.7
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-stringr >=1.3.0
    - r-tibble >=1.4.2
    - r-tidyr >=0.8.0
    - r-viridis >=0.5.0
    - r-visnetwork >=2.0.3

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('DiagrammeR')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('DiagrammeR')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/rich-iannone/DiagrammeR
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: ' Build graph/network structures using functions for stepwise addition and deletion of nodes and edges. Work with data available in tables for bulk addition of nodes, edges, and associated metadata. Use graph selections and traversals to apply changes to specific nodes or edges. A wide selection of graph algorithms
    allow for the analysis of graphs. Visualize the graphs and take advantage of any aesthetic properties assigned to nodes and edges.'
  license_family: MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
